definition: owner/master/host/individual or party concerned/God/Lord/main/to indicate or signify/trump card (in card games)
abbr. for 日本[Ri4 ben3], Japan

sentences.english: For all, we have the Sunday school on Sunday morning.
sentences.chinese: 在星期天的早晨，我們爲大家有主日學。

sentences.english: On Sunday, the first meeting is Sunday School.
sentences.chinese: 我們星期天的第一個聚會是主日學。

sentences.english: Serving as a Sunday School teacher and worship leader in church.
sentences.chinese: 在教會是一名主日學老師，並擔任崇拜領唱。

sentences.english: The Sunday School teacher is expounding scripture right now.
sentences.chinese: 主日學的教師正在講解經文。

sentences.english: Come and meet the kids from our Children Sunday School.
sentences.chinese: 來認識我門的兒童主日學小朋友。

sentences.english: Yes, I have seen homosexual infiltrate the church and Sunday school.
sentences.chinese: 是的，我看過同性戀者滲透教會跟主日學。

sentences.english: Pray for the Sunday School Ministry and teachers.
sentences.chinese: 爲主日學的事工及同工禱告。

definition: to whisper to one another's ear
variant of 定親|定亲[ding4 qin1]
to gesticulate/to make lively gestures (while talking)/also written 比手劃腳|比手划脚
to spike the ball (volleyball etc)/to smash (tennis etc)
